sentences: Jay Ungar (born November 14, 1946) is an American folk musician and composer.
He frequented Greenwich Village music venues during his formative period in the 1960s.
Although he performs with David Bromberg, he is probably best known for "Ashokan Farewell" (1982), composed as a lament, and used as the theme tune to the Ken Burns documentary The Civil War (1990).

In 1991, Ungar married fellow musician Molly Mason.
In 1992, Ungar and Mason provided the soundtrack to the acclaimed documentary film Brother's Keeper, released as a music CD entitled Waltzing with You (1998).
